news.title: A housing shortage is testing Oregon's pioneering land use law; lawmakers are poised to tweak it
news.para: The so-called urban growth boundary, a sacred cow of Oregon's liberal politics, helped to cement the state's green reputation and has been "extremely influential" in its development, said Megan Horst, an urban planning professor at Portland State University.

news.title: UK builders and government need to fix housing shortage, says regulator
news.para: "Housebuilding in Great Britain needs significant intervention so that enough good quality homes are delivered in the places that people need them," Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) Chief Executive Sarah Cardell said.

news.title: Shree Cement receives income tax demand of Rs 261 crore
news.para: Shree Cement in the regulatory filing said that the assessment order was received on February 24, 2024 passed under section 143(3) of Income Tax Act, 1961, pertaining to AY 2021-22, wherein certain additions/disallowances have been made.

news.title: Construction sites in Mumbai made to cough up Rs 83 lakh for pollution
news.para: While 1,572 work sites were levied a penalty of Rs 48 lakh for not keeping their premises clean, 139 sites were fined for burning garbage and 537 individuals for unauthorised dumping of construction and demolition (C&D) waste.

news.title: Kalamassery: 30 houses to be built under 'Snehaveedu'
news.para: Addressing the media here on Saturday, industries minister P Rajeeve said 25 of the 30 houses would be constructed for the families of widows.

news.title: Assess & pay property tax online from next month: Patna civic body
news.para: Patna Municipal Corporation (PMC) has decided to launch ‘identification, assessment, payment and property ID generation (IAPP)’ facility for property owners.

news.title: Odisha extends PMAY-Urban 100-day challenge till end of March
news.para: The department had in November 24, 2023 launched the challenge and decided to reward the best performing ULBs for grounding housing projects under PMAY-U.

news.title: Collect property tax on carpet area only: Karnataka home-owners' plea
news.para: The draft notification issued recently has stated that property tax will be calculated based on the guidance value of the property per square feet per year.

news.title: Transfer fee capped at Rs 25,000, but South Mumbai societies charge Rs 10-30 lakh for selling flats
news.para: The housing society insisted on a share of the sale amount for its NOC to transfer the flat in the name of the new owner. In another south Mumbai building, a seller paid the society Rs 28 lakh for a 2,850sqft flat, reports Nauzer K Bharucha.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh government proposes new township plan near Shimla
news.para: The estimated cost of the project, including land acquisition, is Rs 1,374 crore, town and country planning minister Rajesh Dharani stated in a written reply to Sudhir Sharma, the Congress MLA from Dharamshala.

news.title: Mumbai: Dharavi redevelopment project hits a roadblock over railway land rights
news.para: The Railway Land Development Authority (RLDA) that has signed a lease deed with the Dharavi Redevelopment Project/Slum Redevelopment Authority (DRP/SRA) has refused to allow the land to be sub-leased.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body races against time to collect Rs 700 crore property tax dues in 35 days
news.para: At a time when GHMC is reeling under financial crunch, the officials are under tremendous pressure to achieve the target set for property tax, which funds various development works.

news.title: Upto 100% hike in property rate proposed in Indore's 49 areas
news.para: The district evaluation committee led by collector Asheesh Singh saw senior district registrar Amresh Naydu proposing a rise in the present guideline of property rate to be implemented from April 1, 2024.

news.title: Complete projects on time or face penalties: Maharashtra CM
news.para: While congratulating the winners, Chief Minister Shinde expressed concerns over delays in housing projects and emphasized the need to fulfill the aspirations of applicants waiting for quality homes.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance hopes to earn Rs 5,000 crore profit in FY24
news.para: ​The non-core business includes Loan Against Property (LAP) and affordable housing finance, LIC Housing Finance managing director and CEO Tribhuwan Adhikari told PTI in an interaction.

news.title: Haryana RERA warns Gurugram builders of penalty for delay in filing projects' QPR
news.para: Filing of quarterly progress reports (QPR) and annual audit reports (AARs) by real estate developers is a mandatory requirement under RERA Act 2016.
